<subSubSection id="5ED84742D991AB54E3FAF7A86A0F53E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9DF3F064EB30470D8ED4CCA07D3B7DEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B6FDD505C3E912FE11F2BF4BEB8B9B53" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
Posterior area of hind ocelli depressed inward flatly, forming an acute angle with frons; anterior face of pronotum with one or two foveae in the middle or not obvious, laterally with dense punctures (Figs 
<figureCitation id="4E057B7A82E4D0F0702D7B13DF4B26F3" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BF10F84A8C9D283CEA2A275F30280D17" captionStart="Figures 11–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 11 - 19. Paraleptomenes transfoveolus sp. nov. Holotype (♀) 11, 13, 15, 16, 18, 19 paratype (♂) 12, 14, 17. 11, 12 habitus (dorsal view) 13, 14 head (frontal view) 15 mesosoma (dorsal view) 16 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 17 A 5 - A 13 18 tegula (dorsal view) 19 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures11-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677828" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E7DE50C2BB3C9C22780133AD69C05B83" captionStart="Figures 20–28" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 20 - 28. Paraleptomenes darugiriensis Kumar, Carpenter &amp; Sharma, 2014. ♀ 20, 22, 24, 26, 27, 28 ♂ 21, 23, 25. 20, 21 habitus (dorsal view) 22, 23 head (frontal view) 24 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 25 A 7 - A 13 26 mesosoma (dorsal view) 27 tegula (dorsal view) 28 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures20-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677829" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="5B93CD25D1411334EED57A8BD7773C7D" captionStart="Figures 29–33" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 29 - 33. Paraleptomenes nurseanus montanus Giordani Soika, 1994. ♀ 29 - 33 29 habitus (dorsal view) 30 head (frontal view) 31 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 32 mesosoma (lateral view) 33 mesosoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures29-33" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677830" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">31</figureCitation>
); tegula not reaching posteriorly to the apex of parategula (Figs 
<figureCitation id="F4751FC44B19DF2C97B06B58B84887FA" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="4C2BE590FA3D05D495353DF3AF66DB10" captionStart="Figures 11–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 11 - 19. Paraleptomenes transfoveolus sp. nov. Holotype (♀) 11, 13, 15, 16, 18, 19 paratype (♂) 12, 14, 17. 11, 12 habitus (dorsal view) 13, 14 head (frontal view) 15 mesosoma (dorsal view) 16 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 17 A 5 - A 13 18 tegula (dorsal view) 19 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures11-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677828" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="7F3B4BEAAB0044C8D603AECE80D93337" captionStart="Figures 20–28" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 20 - 28. Paraleptomenes darugiriensis Kumar, Carpenter &amp; Sharma, 2014. ♀ 20, 22, 24, 26, 27, 28 ♂ 21, 23, 25. 20, 21 habitus (dorsal view) 22, 23 head (frontal view) 24 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 25 A 7 - A 13 26 mesosoma (dorsal view) 27 tegula (dorsal view) 28 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures20-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677829" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C4AA96B67431EB3C79C864FA2B708004" captionStart="Figures 29–33" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 29 - 33. Paraleptomenes nurseanus montanus Giordani Soika, 1994. ♀ 29 - 33 29 habitus (dorsal view) 30 head (frontal view) 31 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 32 mesosoma (lateral view) 33 mesosoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures29-33" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677830" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">33</figureCitation>
